#### Q35. What does the code shown below demonstrate, and why?

```cpp
   static void Multiply(int num1, int num2) {};
   static void Multiply(double num1, double num2, double num3) {};
   static void Multiply(float num1, float num2) {};
```

- %OPTION% polymorphism, because each method can perform different task
- %OPTION% method overriding, because it display the same method name, different or same parameters, and same return type
- %OPTION% method overloading, because it allows the creation of several methods with the same name, wich differ by the type of input via parameter
- %OPTION% method overriding, because it display the same method name, different parameters, and same return type

